-- Dow Chemical shares slip
-- 
-- Mon Apr 9, 2007 5:25pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/09/us-markets-stocks-afterthebell-idUSN0934822420070409

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Dow Chemical Co. ( DOW.N ) slipped 1.1 percent after the closing bell on Monday after it said it has had no discussion about a leveraged buyout. The comments follow a report that a consortium of Middle Eastern investors and American buyout firms is preparing a $50 billion approach for the chemical company.  

 Shares slid to $46.10 in electronic trade after closing on the New York Stock Exchange at $46.63. During Monday's regular session, Dow Chemical's stock rose 4.9 percent.